{"id":3045,"date":"2023-10-17T02:10:50","date_gmt":"2023-10-17T02:10:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/?page_id=3045"},"modified":"2023-10-17T02:12:58","modified_gmt":"2023-10-17T02:12:58","slug":"citizenship-naturalization","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/citizenship-naturalization\/","title":{"rendered":"CITIZENSHIP &#038; NATURALIZATION"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"3045\" class=\"elementor elementor-3045\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ab93147 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"ab93147\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6bc13bb e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-child\" data-id=\"6bc13bb\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0db0d6e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0db0d6e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<style>\/*! elementor - v3.21.0 - 08-05-2024 *\/\n.elementor-heading-title{padding:0;margin:0;line-height:1}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title[class*=elementor-size-]>a{color:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-small{font-size:15px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-medium{font-size:19px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-large{font-size:29px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-xl{font-size:39px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-xxl{font-size:59px}<\/style><h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\"> U.S. CITIZENSHIP & NATURALIZATION<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7c13699 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7c13699\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<style>\/*! elementor - v3.21.0 - 08-05-2024 *\/\n.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-stacked .elementor-drop-cap{background-color:#69727d;color:#fff}.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-framed .elementor-drop-cap{color:#69727d;border:3px solid;background-color:transparent}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap{margin-top:8px}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap-letter{width:1em;height:1em}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap{float:left;text-align:center;line-height:1;font-size:50px}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap-letter{display:inline-block}<\/style>\t\t\t\t<p>Once you have obtained a\u00a0green card or permanent residency, your next step will be to apply for U.S. citizenship through the process of\u00a0naturalization. One of the many<strong> benefits of becoming a citizen is that y<\/strong>ou will be able to sponsor family members in their own immigration petitions with the\u00a0immediate relative visa.<\/p><h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 7.8pt 0in .05in 0in;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; color: #47a1e7; letter-spacing: .1pt;\">The most common forms for paths to Citizenship and <\/span><\/b><b><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; color: #00b0f0; letter-spacing: .1pt;\">Naturalization <\/span><\/b><b><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; color: #47a1e7; letter-spacing: .1pt;\">are the:<\/span><\/b><\/h2>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-31a51a8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"31a51a8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">N-400 Application for Naturalization<\/h4>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-dcc4252 testsa elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"dcc4252\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Some of the eligibility requirements to file for Naturalization:<\/strong><\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><ul><li>A green card holder must be at least 18 years of age and must have been a permanent resident for a minimum of 5 years, or 3 years if the applicant is married to a U.S. citizen.<\/li><li>The applicant must have been physically present in the U.S. for half of the 5 year period, or at least 30 months.<\/li><li>The applicant must pass a test of their ability to read, write and speak English, as well as an examination of their knowledge of U.S. history and government.<\/li><li>The applicant must have lived for at least 3 months in the jurisdiction where the application is being filed.<\/li><\/ul><p>\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6834690 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"6834690\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">N-600 Application for Certificate of Citizenship <\/h4>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2dd0993 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2dd0993\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Children under the age of 18 automatically obtain citizenship when their parents are naturalized, so long as the child meets certain residency requirements.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-23171ec elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"23171ec\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 15pt 0in 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/contact-us\/\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; letter-spacing: 0.75pt; color: #3366ff;\">Contact us for more details.<\/span><\/a><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>U.S. CITIZENSHIP &#038; NATURALIZATION Once you have obtained a\u00a0green card or permanent residency, your next step will be to apply for U.S. citizenship through the process of\u00a0naturalization. One of the many benefits of becoming a citizen is that you will be able to sponsor family members in their own immigration petitions with the\u00a0immediate relative visa. [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":"","_links_to":"","_links_to_target":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/3045"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyforusvisas.com\/